3130.Name: Paul Fowler Invitational 2021
3130.Details:
The 2021 Paul Fowler Invitational Platform Tennis Tournament will be played on Saturday, March 13, 2021.  Play will be throughout the day at 16 different clubs across Fairfield County. Details below...

DATE
One-day event on Saturday March 13, 2021.  Seven simultaneous Tournaments, one for each League Division.  
 
FORMAT
Draws will be 16 teams per Division.  The format is designed to provide all participants a minimum of three (3) matches. 

In the case of more than 16 teams, additional 8-team or 16-team draws may be created subject to court availability and enough players
 
ELIGIBILITY
Registration Preference will be provided to players from clubs who have provided courts for the 2021 Paul Fowler Invitational Tournament.  All other players may be used to fill in openings in division draws.  

Both players must be from the same club.  Players must register for the appropriate Tournament (Divisions 1 to 7) based on the Division you played in most frequently this season.  The Tournament Committee reserves the right to adjust a team's division of play based on tournament response and player ability.
 
RULES
APTA rules apply.  Best 2 of 3 sets.  Standard tiebreak at 6 all.  For the first two rounds only, if you split sets, the winner will be determined by playing a “Super tiebreaker” in lieu of a third set – first to win 10 points, must win by 2 points.  
 
LOCATION
Various FCPTL Clubs.  All of your morning matches will be played at one club location.  You will be contacted regarding which club to report to.
 
TIME
Play begins: 8:00 AM for Divisions 1-7. Finals: from 1:00 PM. 


TROPHIES
Prizes will be awarded to the winners of all four draws and finalists in the Main Draw.  Instructions will be provided for players to receive their prizes.
 
LUNCH & AWARDS PRESENTATION
Due to Covid-19, there will be no luncheon or awards presentation this year.
 
SPECTATORS & HEALTH GUIDELINES
Due to Covid-19, there will be no spectators allowed at tournament venues.  Players are expected to comply with all health and safety guideliness of host clubs.
 
ENTRY FEE
$160 per two-man team.
 
ONLINE REGISTRATION PROCESS
Only one player per team needs to complete the on-line registration.  They will pay the full fee and collect half from their partner. To register on line, go to our web site: http://fcptl.paddlescores.com   Look on the horizontal menu on the top of the homepage and click on the words, "Tournaments", then click "Register" next to "Paul Fowler Invitational 2021"

CANCELLATIONS
Cancellations are strongly discouraged.  Any registration canceled before February 20th will be refunded ONLY if a wait-listed team can be added to the tournament.  REFUNDS FOR CANCELLATIONS AFTER  February 20th WILL BE AT THE DISCRETION OF THE FCPTL BOARD.
MATCH LOCATIONS
Everyone will play 3 matches at a single venue before lunch.  Players in 16-team draws: if win your third match, you will have a fourth match in the afternoon.
3130.RegistrationDetails:
To sign up for the 2021 FCPTL Paul Fowler Invitational, only one of the partners needs to complete this on-line form and pay the registration fee via credit card.

If you are not already in the system, you will need to set up an account before you can register.  This is a simple process whereby you enter your name and contact information.

If you have already been entered into the system (this includes all Captains and most players) you will need to use your e-mail address and individual account password to sign in. If you don't know your password, just enter your e-mail address and it will be sent to you.


Please note the following:

1. Choose the appropriate Division (1-7) from the options below.  Players must be from the same club and must register to play in the same Division as the team for which they have played most often during the season.  

2.  Wait List - Once the draws are full (16 teams per division), we will continue to accept a registrations on the wait list in case teams drop out or we need to fill out the draw in another division.  With expectation demand, we will do our best to create additional draws, so please sign up on the Waitlists if you want to play!

3. Cancellations - Completion of the registration process and rendering of payment serves as confirmation of your participation in the tournament.  In case of withdrawal after you have registered, the $160 Tournament Fee will be refunded, ONLY IF YOU FIND A REPLACEMENT TEAM TO TAKE YOUR PLACE and/or at the discretion of the Board.



We will try and assist you in finding a replacement partner or team, but do not guarantee that we will be able to do so.  Any refunds will be processed AFTER the Tournament.


4. Placement - The FCPTL Tournament Committee reserves the right to move teams to a different division based on the need to fill other draws using teams from divisions that are oversubscribed (i.e. more than 16 teams).



The Tournament Committee will make every attempt to limit the need to move teams. We will use our best judgment to ensure that teams are placed in divisions with other teams of similar skill level.

Good luck to all teams in the Tournament!



FCPTL Board

3544.Name: CCNC - Men's Club Championship
3544.Details:
Gentlemen, the draw is out!


Please schedule the matches on your own when the time works for all 4 players. 

You will have a deadline that will need to be respected and strongly reinforced! 


The winning team will report the score to me and should reach out to the opponents in the next round. There will be a reprieve draw so not all is lost after the first loss.


•The round of 32 has 2 matches and should be scheduled asap.


•The 1/8 (the first match for most of you) should be completed by January 20th


•The 1/4 finals should be completed by February 15th (please be aware of the school breaks in February and don’t wait too long to schedule this round)


•The semifinals should be completed by March 1st



•The final match will be on March 10th, 2022 at 6pm (before the men’s Thursday night ).



The courts can be an issue if you try to reserve it last minute. Feel free to email me and I will do my very best to accommodate you especially knowing that it’s hard to round up 4 players. The match ball and a warmup ball will be at the front desk of the main clubhouse and available at all times.
